/** Description **/

A secure on-device micro web server for accessing variety of files, including IOCipher-based encrypted file systems,
via a web HTML interface or a mountable WebDav service.

- Does *NOT* require root or any special or extended priveleges

- Includes ability to enable HTTPS/SSL support in server by autogenerating a local,
self-signed SSL keypair and certificate.

- Uses mDNS to announce the availability of https and webdav(s) services

- Will incorporate the IOCipher project: https://github.com/guardianproject/IOCipherServer

/**** Includes ****/

Tiny Java Web Server
http://tjws.sourceforge.net/

Milton: Java WebDav API
http://milton.ettrema.com/

SpongyCastle (BouncyCastle repackaged)
https://github.com/rtyley/spongycastle

Simple Logging Facade for java
http://www.slf4j.org/

Apache Commons (IO, File Utils)
http://commons.apache.org/

JDOM
http://jdom.org
